name: Anna maria island
summary: Anna Maria Island, a popular tourist destination, has been impacted by a series of recent events. A fire broke out at a home, causing damage. Hurricane Helene brought flooding, leading to some residents ignoring evacuation orders. The storm also caused significant damage to Holmes Beach, with officials considering cutting services to Anna Maria Island in preparation. Flooding remained an issue in Holmes Beach, while a water shut-off was in effect for both Manatee and Sarasota counties, including Anna Maria Island and Siesta Key. Furthermore, bridges to Anna Maria Island were closed for an extended period, hampering access to the area. The hurricane's impact has been documented through live streams and residents expressed devastation in the aftermath.

name: Presidents Cup
summary: The Presidents Cup is an international golf tournament held every two years between a team from the United States and an International team made up of players from outside the United States and Europe. The 2024 Presidents Cup will be held at Royal Montreal Golf Club in Montreal, Canada, from September 19-25, 2024. The U.S. team is the defending champion, having won the 2022 Presidents Cup at Quail Hollow Club in Charlotte, North Carolina. The International team is looking to win its first Presidents Cup since 2019. The Presidents Cup format consists of 30 matches, with 18 four-ball matches, 12 foursomes matches, and 6 singles matches. The team with the most points at the end of the tournament wins the Presidents Cup. The 2024 Presidents Cup is expected to be a closely contested tournament, with both teams fielding strong teams. The U.S. team is led by Scottie Scheffler, the world's No. 1 ranked player, while the International team is led by Cameron Smith, the world's No. 3 ranked player.

name: Oakland as
summary: The Oakland Athletics are bidding farewell to their Oakland home after 57 years. The departure is met with mixed emotions, with some fans expressing sadness and others relief at the departure of an inept owner and MLB enablers. The city of Oakland is coming to grips with the loss of its only major professional sports team, as the A's prepare to move to Las Vegas. Despite the departure, the A's final game in Oakland was a sellout, with fans paying tribute to the team's legacy and sharing memories of their time at the Coliseum. The departure also raised questions about the future of the Oakland Coliseum and the legacy of the A's in the city.
